  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/noncannulated-not-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Not accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment is Not accepted based on documented shortfalls in three factors at model risk level 3. (1) Discretization error: achieved Gradation 2 against required Gradation 3. The coarse-to-fine mesh variation of 6.1% exceeds the 5% acceptance threshold; GCI of 3.8% is acceptable but insufficient alone to satisfy Gradation 3 without the coarse-to-fine criterion being met. (2) Model inputs: achieved Gradation 2 against required Gradation 3. Primary material properties were drawn from published datasheets rather than lot-specific coupon measurements, and UHMWPE block modulus was taken from ASTM F648 nominal rather than measured from the actual test lot. These input uncertainties are not fully characterized and cannot be offset by output comparison results alone. (3) Test conditions: achieved Gradation 2 against required Gradation 3. All validation testing was conducted under a single F1717 condition with one rod diameter and one loading rate, providing insufficient coverage of the COU operating envelope. Gradation 3 requires at least two systematically varied conditions. No offset rationale is claimed for any of these shortfalls. Remediation path: (a) refine mesh to achieve coarse-to-fine variation below 5% and re-run GCI; (b) conduct lot-specific coupon testing for Ti-6Al-4V and UHMWPE and update model inputs accordingly; (c) add at least one additional test condition varying rod diameter or loading rate within the operating envelope.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
